threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a malicious IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of the Gafgyt (Bashlite) or Mirai families, targeting mipsel-based Linux devices. It exhibits several definitive malicious behaviors: it implements a downloader routine (sub_40af24) that fetches architectural variants from a hardcoded C2 at 89.116.20.194:81; it features an aggressive process killer (sub_403868) that iterates through /proc to identify and terminate competing malware and diagnostic tools (wget, curl, ftp, ps, netstat); and it includes a watchdog suppression routine (sub_40582c) to prevent system reboots. Furthermore, it contains a password-protected backdoor shell (sub_407c4c) and hardcoded commands for architecture-specific payload delivery and execution via /bin/busybox.
